                " \n \nBRAND MANAGER\nLocation: Bryanston, Head Office\nCompany: Nestle\nQualification: Commercial Degree or Equivalent\nExperience: A minimum of 3 years in marketing experience (including commercial function Sales, CCSD & FMCG)\nClosing Date: 10 May 2024\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We\u2019re now looking for a Brand Manager for our Nestle Infant Nutrition NAN brand. The role will lead strategy development & execution for sustainable, profitable of this highly purposeful brand.\n \nA day in the life of the Brand Manager for NIDO:\nKnow your consumer deeply - understand the consumer behavior by conducting qualitative and quantitative studies in liaison with the local research team and research partners.\nInspire with Brand Vision and Essence - Deeply understand, actively and consistently ensure the Brand Essence governs everything the brand says and does.\nDelight with Product & Packaging Experience Deliver the tastiest and healthiest products as perceived by target consumers and in comparison, with competition. Champion development of relevant and preferred packaging & product solutions to improve the consumer experience. Manage the brand to enhance our Nutrition, Health & Wellness goals.\nWin with Shoppers - Understand the relevant shopping environment & behaviour and how these can be leveraged to delight shoppers and improve performance. Define the desired relative price of products within the brand \u2013 and versus other brands/products \u2013 so it is aligned with consumers\u2019 perceived value relative to competitors and portfolio strategy.\nInnovate Bigger Bolder Better - Passionately seek out ideas and leverage internal & external resources to contribute to the development of an innovation pipeline. Ensure consumer-centricity, apply Innovation levers, maintain vibrancy via relevant innovation & renovation for our brands to deliver against commercial objectives. Accountable and responsible for providing quality Concept briefs to the I&R and Project Managers and managing execution.\nPlan and Executive Flawlessly - Contribute to the development and execution of a strong, cross-functionally aligned brand and Integrated Commercial Plan. Track and monitor the performance, health, and strategic alignment of the brand. Understand & manage the business impact of marketing spend (PFME) of the brand portfolio.\nCreate Engaging Brand Experiences - Contribute and manage the development process of creating Ownable Brand Propositions and Big Ideas. Work in partnership with communication agencies to develop engaging & effective communication. Ensure all brand communication contributes to enhancing the company image of the trusted NHW leader. Embraces e-business and digital to drive brand and business performance.\nFinancial & Business Acumen - PFME Budget management and P&L understanding to enable strategic decision-making & growth choices.\n \nWhat will make you successful:\nMinimum 3 years\u2019 experience in Marketing or in another commercial function e.g. Sales, CCSD (FMCG food experience or Pharmaceutical preferable)\nProven track record to work independently\nExperience working in cross-functional teams\nBachelor's Degree/IMM Diploma (Marketing Preferred)\nWorks well in high-performing, fast-paced environment\nHas contributed to the development and implementation of business strategy aimed at increasing brand competitiveness.\n \nBryanston, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "LABORATORY ADMINISTRATOR\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9 Clayville\nQualification:  Matric \nExperience: 2 years\u2019 experience in Laboratory administration   \nClosing Date: 08 May 2024                                                                                                                           \n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Laboratory Administrator to be based in Clayville. \nIn this role you will be responsible to Co- ordinate sample management related activities and support NQAC Clayville with non - analytical activities such as procurement, customer administration and GLOBE SAP LIMS\n\nA day in the life of a Laboratory Administrator:\nLaboratory Support and Services Activities\nOn time sample registration, acknowledgement and ensure good traceability of samples.\nGood inventory control on supply of reagents and materials needed for the lab use.\n Responsible for common laboratory and non-laboratory materials procurement activities e.g., purchase requisition, contact of vendors / goods receipt.\nCustomer/ Administrative\nServe as Customers contact point in terms of enquiry (method capability, samples priorities request).\nMain contact for samples handling, import / export permits (samples and materials)\nEnsure effective and efficient communication with customers.\nEnsure all enquiries and Complaints are handled and follow up on time.\nAssist Customer in matter related to GLOBE-QM (inspection plan set up, Master data setup. etc.)\nProvide support to NQAC users and Market in matters related to Globe LIMS & GLCA. \n  Globe-SAP LIMS\nGLOBE-LIMS (Master Inspection plans, reception, Sub-division, Internal issues resolving, storage and disposal etc.)\nGLOBE-LIMS (Communication with all customers, analytical Billing, ISO reports)\nProvide GLOBE-LIMS training to NQACs users and the Market.\nPR Creation\nCreate purchase requisitions into SAP in accordance with policy parameters.\nMaintain, expedite, and report on past due POs within AMM.\nResolve blocked payment invoices of SAP workflow notification.\nResolve GRIR reports.\nGeneral Services\nAssisting in workshop for logistic support e.g., beverages, tea break etc. if called upon.\nAppointed as Globe LIMS/GLCA super user for the NQAC Clayville and for the Market        \n                            \nWhat will make you successful?\nMatric\nMin 2 yrs. experience in Laboratory administration \nSAP knowledge and basic understanding of Microbiological and Chemistry Analysis.\n Good understanding of English and basic statistics\n Operational Experience \nProficient in MS Office           \n \nBryanston, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                "CATEGORY TECHNICAL EXPERT\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nQualification:  Degree: Food Science or Chemical Engineering\n\nExperience:  5 years experience in Production Environment\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Category Technical Expert to be based in Bryanston.\n\nIn this role you will be responsible for Idea to Launch Market projects and Technical support to factories for Operations optimization and Capability building.\n \nA day in the life of a Category Technical Expert:\nFacilitate seamless implementation of new products and technologies, overseeing the entire process from R&D to operations.\nDrive the successful completion of development projects, ensuring they progress smoothly from initial concept to post-launch evaluation.\nLead projects and initiatives focused on enhancing products, processes, and supplier relationships, such as cost reduction, supplier development, and specification optimization.\nDevelop and sustain expertise in product and process mastery, enabling manufacturing operations to achieve zero defects.\nServe as a vital link between the market and R&D, ensuring effective communication and alignment of objectives.\nProvide comprehensive technical support to address basic assistance requests from factories.\nPromote knowledge transfer to factories, empowering them with product and process mastery to eliminate waste and optimize efficiency (e.g., ZLMV and EUPS).\n \nWhat will make you successful?\nDegree: Food Science and Chemical Engineering\n5 years\u2019 experience in production environment (Plant Manager).\nEnglish speaking, as needed (e.g., suppliers abroad)\nDisciplined\nEye for detail- Able to balance priorities.\nAble to see the bigger picture beyond the scope of their job.\nThinks outside of the box.\n Can challenge the current status quo.\n \nBryanston, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW",
                "MARKETING EFFECTIVENESS MANAGER\nLocation: Bryanston, Head Office\nQualification: BSc Data Science and Business or BCom in Mathematics or Data\nExperience: A minimum of 2 - 5 years\u2019 experience within a Sales/ Business/ Marketing Analyst or a Data Specialists in commercial functions or brands\nClosing Date: 6 May 2024\n \nPosition Summary\nOwns the Marketing Effectiveness Programme.  Performs qualitative and quantitative analysis to ensure efficiency and effectiveness of marketing investments. Partners with cross functional teams to ensure brand and portfolio strategies are aligned. Responsible for the marketing ROI programme as a priority and implementing the programme in market. This includes, but is not limited to, upskilling cross functional teams on the programme.\n \nA day in the life of the Marketing Effectiveness Specialist:\nProgram management in market:\nCollaborate closely with the data quality lead in identifying the type of data needed to be further input to the model.\nRecommend additional data to be acquired to increase the accuracy of the model if needed.\nWork closely with the analytics service line hub to deliver the planned Marketing Mix Modelling (MMM) across the brand portfolios by being their spokesperson in the market, bringing local expertise related to data specificities, business activities and category/brand specificities.\nCo-lead the model validation to ensure high quality and explain ability of the model.\nAssume responsibility as subject matter expert locally in evangelizing MMM methodology /benefits associated, demonstrate the capabilities of predictive models in specific trainings as needed and respond to questions from internal stakeholders.\nSupport the embedding of effectiveness metrics in the various business process.\nData to insights:\nSupport the brand teams in turning model results from the app into concrete insights related to activations effectiveness overall (trade & consumer promotions, media and CRM and detailed campaign optimization).\nCollaborate with media agencies to make them familiar with the learnings and partner closely with them to integrate them into their media plan recommendations.\nIdentify meta learnings at market level in terms of portfolio choice, activation mechanics and media channels/plans in terms of effectiveness associated with brand objective.\nWork closely with the insights team to ensure that all insights learnings are effectively utilised to get the most out of the programme.\nMarket value realization\nEffectively communicate status and progress of the program to global and local leadership teams and various stakeholders.\nProject management of the programme.\nTrack and report overall effectiveness of the program through specific KPIs\n \nWhat will make you successful\nBSc Data Science and Business or BCom in Mathematics or Data\nA minimum of 2-5 years\u2019 experience within a Sales/ Business/ Marketing Analyst or a Data Specialists in commercial functions or brands\nMust understand data and be commercially savvy\nMust have project management skills\nMust understand marketing and media\nExperienced partnering with cross-functional teams is required\nMust be comfortable with doing presentations\n \nBryanston, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW"
