                "SUPPLY CHAIN GRADUATE\nAPPLY\nLocations ZAF - Cape Town\nTime type Full time\nJob requisition id R67860\nRole Title   Supply Chain Graduate \nLocation   Cape Town \nRewards Competitive salary and comprehensive benefits on offer\n\nSummary\nAt Smith+Nephew, we believe in our products. We believe that through innovation, development and supporting our customers and patients we can help others achieve a Life Unlimited!\nAn excellent opportunity has arisen within our Supply Chain Division for a Loan Set Controller in Port Elisabeth. The incumbent is responsible for all functions related to Loan set/Inventory management, i.e., preparation. kit filling, kit maintenance, washing of instrumentation, checking of instrumentation, ordering of inventory for loan set requirements, etc. Reverse logistics, ensure physical checking of all returns and correct updating on the computer system.\nSound Exciting? We believe so!\n \nKey Performance Areas\nTo ensure that loan sets are complete and correct for customer delivery.\nTo ensure that deliveries take place on schedule.\nTo inspect all items to ensure that they are in working condition.\nTo ensure that Safety Stock levels are maintained.\n \nKey Functions/Tasks \nTogether with the Customer Services Department, ensures that all bookings made, either by a Customer or the Sales force, is executed at a very high standard, i.e.\nSets/stock to be delivered within the required time to the Customer.\nEnsures that Loan Sets are complete, implants correspond with the required pick list/check list, and that all instruments are in working condition and complete as per the check list\nAdvises the Sales force of any discrepancies with regard to Loan Sets in the office or received back from the Customer.\nEnsures that all usages are identified and verified by the Customer Services Officer.\nIn conjunction with the Supervisor, co-ordinates the delivery schedule for the day, and ensures that the Field Assistants understand and execute the required tasks\nEnsures that all Loan Sets, Check Lists (Implants) are verified against the AS400/LANSA systems.\nEnsures that all Capital, Demo and Loan equipment is controlled, monitored and issued on LANSA.\nEnsures that all Capital items on loan are accompanied by a Loan Agreement form, which must be signed by the Customer.\nDemo Trolley bookings must be co-ordinated between the CSO, the Sales Manager and the incumbent.\nEnsures that all Capital, Demo, Loan items are in working condition, and inspected on a regular basis, in conjunction with the S&N Clinical Engineer\nCo-ordinates all repairs (Endo) being done, and checks with the CSO that the repairs are recovered and invoiced.\nTogether with the Operations Manager and Team Leader, ensures that all stock on the shelf corresponds with what is on the AS400 system.  Discrepancies must be investigated and reported to the Operations Manager.\nPlans and receives Inter-Depot transfers, ensures that Safety Stock levels are maintained, and that timeous ordering of stock occurs.  Picks, issues and confirms all Inventory transactions on LANSA.\nAssists with stock takes when required.\nAssists with deliveries / collections when required.\nWorks on a shift basis.\nEnsures that the working environment is safe at all times, neat, clean and risk-free.\nMaintains company vehicles.\n \nMinimum Entry Requirements\nEducation\nMatriculation\nDegree or Diploma in Supply Chain Management\n \nExperience\nComputer literate, and knowledge of ERP systems would be advantageous."
