                "BRAND MANAGER\nLOCATION SOUTH AFRICA - JOHANNESBURGCATEGORY MARKETING\nAPPLY NOW\n \nJOB PURPOSE AND SCOPE:\nAt Abbott, diverse ideas, perspectives, and expertise allow us to create the life-changing solutions that help people live healthier lives. In 150 countries and with businesses spanning nutrition, diagnostics, medical devices, and branded generic pharmaceuticals, Abbott offers you opportunities to explore your\ninterests and help you achieve your career and personal goals.\nIn this role, the Brand Manager, is responsible to uncover consumer and customer insights, deliver innovative marketing campaigns and generate strategies that grow market share and the brand\u2019s reputation, improve customer experience and drive sales and margin growth.\nLeads and directs all marketing activities for the assigned brand or business to achieve growth, market share and profit objectives in line with the overall business priorities.\nLeads the implementation of the omni-channel (i.e., integrating traditional, digital, and CRM channels to deliver a unified customer experience) marketing strategy and tactics and provide appropriate support to affiliates to assure the commercial success of assigned Abbott Diabetes Care brands.\nPlan, develop and direct marketing efforts for Abbott Diabetes Care brands available in South Africa, to ensure profitable growth.\n\nCORE JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:\n1. Accountable for designated portfolio performance as per communicated quarterly / annual targets.\n2. Prepare, coordinate, support and implement annual brand plans.\n3. Initiate and oversee planning of healthcare professional (HCP), hospitals and pharmacy\npromotion to drive performance of products within portfolio. Determine to-market strategies and sales tactics to achieve sales objectives.\n4. Management of agencies to implement plans, create promotional material.\n5. Ensure sales force adoption of key promotional activities through product and campaign training to sales force on a regular basis.\n6. Monitoring of allocated annual advertising and promotion (A&P) budgets.\n7. Review promotional budget monthly, manage changes as required and communicate at proposed forecast stage.\n8. Ensuring that the product and marketing efforts are aligned with company\u2019s overall strategy and goals.\n9. Ensure up to date promotional material are localized from global baseline material, approved in Veeva by all relevant approvers and in line with ADC Promo Standard Operating Procedures\n10. Maintain up to date promotional item trackers and manage the allocation of promo items accordingly.\n11. Creating monthly social media messaging themes, approved content and overseeing the community management thereof.\n12. Assist with planning, securing approvals and execution of external HCP meetings and events.\n13. Assist with planning and execution of internal sales meetings.\n14. Point of contact for all compliance related questions from OEC relevant to marketing initiatives, events and HCP agreements\n15. Coordinating the formulation of sound marketing strategies for each promoted product in line with marketing excellence principles as well as portfolio, financial and strategic objectives to ensure full implementation.\n16. Understanding financial and business considerations impacting both the company capabilities and readiness to support a strategic drive via new product and/or service introduction.\n17. Developing and sustaining productive customer relationships.\n18. Managing company resources consistent with company compliance and quality policies to achieve organizational goals.\n19. Maintain rapport with national key opinion leaders in the market to identify trends, competitor activities and new opportunities.\n20. Ensure monthly field visits are organized with individual representatives both for personal development and solid feedback of the strategies.\n\nMinimum Skills Required: Experience Required:\n\u2022 Understanding of digital marketing\n\u2022 Sound organizational skills, financial acumen and ability to multi-task.\n\u2022 Product launch and brand planning experience is\n\u2022 Strong interpersonal relations and customer focus.\n\u2022 Strong ability to interpret sales & marketing figures + market / trend analysis.\n\u2022 Proven ability to positively influence cross functional teams, or individual team members without formal authority.\n\u2022 Energetic, self \u2013 starter, reliable and proven customer centric approach.\n\u2022 Excellent written and verbal communication skills.\n\u2022 Computer literacy: Excel, PowerPoint, is essential.\n\u2022 Minimum of 5 years sales or brand management experience within medical\ndevices preferred.\n\u2022 Experience in working with market data / market analysis (IMS, Impact Rx, etc.)\n\u2022 Understanding and knowledge of the diabetes market in South Africa, including key opinion leaders.\n \nKnowledge / Education Required:\n\u2022 Tertiary qualification in Health Sciences and/or Business Sciences or equivalent.\n\u2022 Experience in sales or marketing of medical devices\n\u2022 Additional, Marketing qualification/IMM/Commercial qualification \n \nAPPLY NOW \n \nJOB ID 31083537\nLOCATION South Africa \u2013 Johannesburg\nMEDICAL SURVEILLANCE No\nDIVISIONADC Diabetes Care \nTRAVEL Yes, 75 % of the Time\nADDITIONAL LOCATION\nSIGNIFICANT WORK ACTIVITIES Not Applicable",
                "CUSTOMER SERVICE COORDINATOR INTERNSHIP\nLOCATION SOUTH AFRICA - JOHANNESBURG\nCATEGORY BUSINESS SUPPORT\nAPPLY NOW\nJOB TITLE: CUSTOMER SERVICES CO-ORDINATOR INTERNSHIP (1-YEAR FIXED-TERM CONTRACT)\n \nABOUT ABBOTT\nAbbott is a global healthcare leader, creating breakthrough science to improve people\u2019s health. We\u2019re always looking towards the future, anticipating changes in medical science and technology.\n \nWORKING AT ABBOTT\nAt Abbott, you can do work that matters, grow, and learn, care for yourself and family, be your true self and live a full life. You will have access to:\nCareer development with an international company where you can grow the career you dream of.\nA company recognized as a great place to work in dozens of countries around the world and named one of the most admired companies in the world by Fortune.\nA company that is recognized as one of the best big companies to work for as well as a best place to work for diversity, working mothers, female executives, and scientists.\n \nTHE OPPORTUNITY\nThis position works out of our Johannesburg location in the Abbott Core Diagnostics Division. We\u2019re empowering smarter medical and economic decision making to help transform the way people manage their health at all stages of life. Every day, more than 10 million tests are run on Abbott\u2019s diagnostics instruments, providing lab results for millions of people. Our diagnostic solutions are used in hospitals, laboratories and clinics around the globe. The crucial information derived from our tests, instruments and informatics systems are often the first step in patient care decision making for hundreds of health conditions from heart attacks to blood disorders to infectious diseases and cancers.\nThe role of the Customer Service Coordinator intern will be instrumental in supporting and assisting the Supply Chain department in the following duties:\n \nWHAT YOU\u2019LL DO:\nDATA CAPTURING\nEnsure that all orders are captured onto data sheet (orders tracker)\nORDER HANDLING & DISTRIBUTION\nReceives orders via Internet, fax or mail, and distribute amongst the team to ensure captured within the order cut off SLA.\nFirst response handling (to ensure instruction has been actioned)\nTo ensure all stages of the order process are captured accurately with reference to system data and times processed by order entry team on the data sheet adding necessary information. (If required).\nEnters the order, taking into consideration any special-order types or FOC codes. Specific customer requests. (If required).\nFollows up on Back Order Report daily with communication to customers using a template.\nEnsure contact details present for automatic order conformation.\nQUERIES HANDLING (COMPLAINTS)\nReceives customer complaints specific to order responsibility.\nClear Back Order report received from customers.\nADMINISTRATIVE TASKS\nEnsuring each order has relevant correspondence attached.\nCALL HANDLING.\nRecords all incoming calls from customers on the customer care line, ensuring follow-up with customer within 24 hours.\nDistributing workload within the team\nAD-HOC DEPARTMENT REQUESTS\nCompletion of tasks assigned of a general nature to assist the division achieving department goals including entering an order using ADOC system, taking into consideration any special-order types or FOC codes. Specific customer requests. (If required).\nCUSTOMER FOCUS\nMaking customer needs the primary focus of one\u2019s actions.\nActively seeks information to understand customers\u2019 circumstances, problems, expectations, and needs.\nShares information with customers to build their understanding of issues and capabilities.\nBuilds rapport and co-operative relationships with customers.\nConsiders how actions or plans will affect customers; responds quickly to meet customer needs and resolve problems; avoids over commitments.\n \nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS\nTertiary qualification, preferably in Supply Chain, Logistics or related.\nNO EXPERIENCE is preferred- i.e the organization is seeking to hire newly graduated candidates.\nMust live in Johannesburg.\nExcellent Communication skills.\nBasic skills in Microsoft Excel, Word and PowerPoint.\nTelephonic skills required.\n \nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\nAble to speak, read and write English.\nWorking within a team.\nTaking ownership\nAdherence to work and being available to ensure that client expectation is met.\n \n \nFollow your career aspirations to Abbott for diverse opportunities with a company that can help you build your future and live your best life. Abbott is an Equal Opportunity Employer, committed to employee diversity.\n \nConnect with us at www.abbott.com, on Facebook at www.facebook.com/Abbott  and on Twitter @AbbottNews and @AbbottGlobal. \n \nAPPLY NOW \n \nJOB ID 31083398\nLOCATION South Africa \u2013 Johannesburg\nMEDICAL SURVEILLANCE No\nDIVISION HIAC Core Lab\nTRAVEL No\nADDITIONAL LOCATION\nSIGNIFICANT WORK ACTIVITIES Not Applicable"
